---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
---

<Layout title="My Journey | Ernests Smalikis">
		<Navbar />
		<main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
			<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">🛠️ My Journey</h1>
				<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg mb-8">
					<p class="text-lg mb-4">
						I began by building small tools — a password generator, custom scripts, and local automation systems — often under constraint, such as failing hardware or lack of access to industry-standard infrastructure. But constraint bred innovation.
					</p>
					
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">Key Milestones</h2>
					<ul class="space-y-4 mb-6">
						<li class="flex items-start">
							<span class="text-blue-600 mr-2">✓</span>
							<span>Bootstrapped my career without external funding or formal backing</span>
						</li>
						<li class="flex items-start">
							<span class="text-blue-600 mr-2">✓</span>
							<span>Survived and rebuilt workflows after hardware breakdowns</span>
						</li>
						<li class="flex items-start">
							<span class="text-blue-600 mr-2">✓</span>
							<span>Learned through real-world trial and error — not just tutorials</span>
						</li>
						<li class="flex items-start">
							<span class="text-blue-600 mr-2">✓</span>
							<span>Balanced development with a military role, reinforcing discipline and resilience</span>
						</li>
						<li class="flex items-start">
							<span class="text-blue-600 mr-2">✓</span>
							<span>Took on real client projects, handling pressure and scope shifts with professionalism</span>
						</li>
					</ul>
					
					<p class="text-lg italic border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 mt-6">
						Every challenge became a stepping stone. I'm not where I want to be yet — but every day, I build closer to that.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
</Layout>
